# [[preputial]]

====Usage notes====
One sometimes encounters the spelling {{m|fr||prépucial}}, which may seem appropriate given the spelling of the root word {{m|fr|prépuce}}. However, that word derives from the Latin {{m|la|praeputium}}; its spelling with ''-ce'' reflects its modern French pronunciation while conceding to the standard orthography of modern French, in which the ''-uce'' represents {{IPAchar|/-ys/}} where the spelling ''-ute'' — closer to the Latin spelling — would represent {{IPAchar|/-yt/}}. As the sequence ''-tia-'' is usually read as {{IPAchar|/-sja-/}} in contemporary French, the spelling of '''{{m|fr||préputial}}''' is able to follow the form of the Latin etymon while remaining in accord of normative French orthography.

